# OpenShift + RHOAI Manifest Rules

## YAML formatting

- Use 2-space indentation ‚Äî never tabs
- Use `.yaml` extension (not `.yml`)
- One resource per file ‚Äî name the file after the resource kind or purpose (e.g., `deployment.yaml`, `cluster-queue.yaml`)
- Order top-level keys: `apiVersion` > `kind` > `metadata` > `spec` > `data`/`stringData`
- Use block style for multi-line strings (`|` for literal, `>` for folded)
- End files with a single newline
- Use `true`/`false` for booleans ‚Äî never `yes`/`no`

## Doc-validated schemas only
- If editing/creating CRs (Operators, CRDs, custom resources), verify the schema first:
  - `oc explain <kind>`
  - `oc get crd <name> -o yaml` (to confirm versions/fields)
- Do not "guess" fields based on other versions or upstream projects.

## Version alignment
- Ensure all manifests align with:
  - RHOCP 4.20 behaviors/APIs
  - RHOAI 3.3 operator/CR APIs
- If the cluster exposes different API versions than expected, call it out and adapt the manifest accordingly.

## Every step must include validation
When adding a manifest, also provide:
- How to confirm the operator reconciled it (events/status conditions)
- The minimal `oc` commands to verify it works

## YAML comment hygiene

Comments in YAML manifests must explain **why**, never restate **what**.

### Do NOT add
- **Title comments** that restate the `kind` ‚Äî the YAML already says `kind: Namespace`.
  Bad: `# Namespace for Kueue Operator`
  Bad: `# OperatorGroup for Authorino`
  Bad: `# MariaDB Service for Model Registry`
- **Decorative section headers** ‚Äî no `# ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê`, `# ===`, `# ---` borders.
- **Blank spacer lines** (`#` with no text) between comment lines.
- **Field narration** ‚Äî do not narrate obvious fields.
  Bad: `# Use ingress from OpenShift routes` above `ingress.istio.enabled: false`
  Bad: `# High availability configuration` above `high-availability:`
  Bad: `# AWS S3-compatible credentials` above `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID:`

### DO add
- **Why / design decisions**: explain non-obvious choices, workarounds, caveats.
- **Ref links**: `# Ref: https://docs.redhat.com/...`
- **Warnings**: `# DEMO VALUES ONLY`, `# IMPORTANT:`, `# NOTE (RHOAI 3.3):`
- **Constraints**: things that will break if changed (e.g., ordering, naming conventions).

### kustomization.yaml resources lists
List resources without per-resource comments unless the entry has a non-obvious reason:
```yaml
resources:
  - namespace.yaml
  - operatorgroup.yaml
  - subscription.yaml
  # Must be created before DataScienceCluster
  - dsci.yaml
```

## Agent Behavior

After modifying Kubernetes/OpenShift YAML manifests:
- Verify the manifest has correct key ordering (`apiVersion` > `kind` > `metadata` > `spec`)
- If the file is part of a Kustomize base, run `kustomize build <base-path>` to verify it renders
- For new or significantly changed manifests, validate with `kustomize build <path> | oc apply --dry-run=server -f -`
- Verify the target cluster context before suggesting `oc apply` commands: `oc whoami` and `oc project`
- Scope operations to an explicit namespace ‚Äî never rely on the default namespace
- After mutations, confirm resource state: `oc get <resource> -n <namespace>`
- When removing a resource from `kustomization.yaml`, also delete the unreferenced file to prevent orphaned manifests
